name: Brent C
text: Papa Murphy's is consistent in the taste, quality and service delivered.  Being able to bake your own pizza is an awesome business model.  The freshest pizza, hot from the oven, and ready when you are ready.  Amazing.  Wish we had one closer to us.

name: Mark Cox
text: it's really good pizza and it gives you something to do instead of just ordering delivery you can go out get a pizza go home and bake it

name: Jordan Fisher
text: Papa Murphy’s is the best when you want fresh pizza but don’t want to make it yourself. Great food and will always go back!

name: Kris DeWitt
text: Discovered Papa Murphy’s while living in Colorado. I was pleased to find one close to us in Oviedo. Fresh pizza (it should be since it is not cooked yet), good cookie dough, and friendly staff. I really like their pizza sauce for dipping. A little sweet and a little tangy. Nice stuff.

name: G F
text: We are so sad to hear about this shop closing!  Was our favorite local place to grab a pizza.  Opted for this over closer, already baked, places.

name: Sean Bowmer
text: $10 Tuesdays are awesome! Get the pizza you want with all the toppings and then bake it to perfection at home! The ladies were very nice and the pizza is great.

name: Patricia Cox
text: Great pizza. Slower service than I am use to. But pretty fast.

name: Ahmed Elsadek
text: It was my first time there today and the old lady was not welcoming and spoke with an unfriendly tone of voice. My friends also felt the same and we decided to leave immediately.  I don’t think I will ever visit that place again.

name: Nancy Williams
text: My family and I love Papa Murphys.  So sad to see the Winter Springs location is closing.  We started going there when the Lake Mary location closed.

name: Leslie Hage
text: Pizza was ready as promised.  Fresh ingredients that you bake, yourself!  Stuffed pizza is the best!

name: Todd Persons
text: So convenient...cook it when your ready... The thin-crust Veggie is my fav...takes 10 minutes

name: Jennifer Sparkman
text: Always friendly staff, the pizza is take and bake. So it's super fresh and really tasty! I always get the thin crust and usually the chicken artichoke and the roasted garlic Angus steak pizza . You can call ahead and order or order online …More

name: Christina Soberon-Llort
text: Surprisingly good take n bake pizza.  Very good ingredients for the price, and the employees are always very friendly.

name: Mohamed Fahim KONGA
text: I went with my friends for the first time and the old lady working there was very rude , unfriendly and unhelpful at all. Please hire more professional people that can help you to get more customers not losing them .

name: Kimberley Lake de Pulla
text: Dinner saver and always friendly smiling faces

name: rory jacobs
text: Quick and easy! Staffs was friendly and pizza was delicious

name: Panther Pond
text: The pizza is pretty good, not too greasy. The front people are friendly and helpful.

name: Jonathan Rincon
text: Dumbest idea I have ever heard of. I went in to eat some pizza with my family only to find out they make a Pizza so you can bake at YOUR OWN HOME. Left there as quickly as possible and went to a real pizza restaurant.

name: Diana Delgado
text: It has the feel of a subway restaurant and a wawa gas station combined.... the representatives were pleasant but no one warned me I wasn't getting a COOKED pizza. I paid 30 bucks to eat out and I still had to cook it? No boo boo.... they need to charge less for that type of service.  I was extremely disappointed.

name: Robert Finnerty
text: Great quality and great taste

name: Angeline Gores
text: They are always awesome!  I love coming and grabbing a pizza.  I get their salad for lunch sometimes and their cookies are amazing!  Great service!

name: Giselle Reyes
text: Great. I love their pizzas. Wish there was one closer.

name: Emi Clar
text: Their Veggie Delite is my all time favorite pizza! Our 6-year-old loves it too!!

name: Alex Roberts
text: Drove an hour round trip for this pizza. It's amazing. Wish there was one closer to me! Great service, fantastic pizza.

name: Ronald Murray
text: I love this place and their gluten free crust..

name: Peni Nicholas
text: Favorite pizza place...so quick to cook and freshly delicious

name: Elvis Kalicharan
text: It's so amazing and the people are great

name: Jonathan Hernandez
text: Delicious pizza. Good selection. Nice staff.

name: Marina Sosa
text: We got two X-LARGE pizza and we had so much left over. Everything was fresh

name: Cale Schmidt
text: So far I have gone 3 times and they got them all right.  I'm actually gonna get some tonight.  I love their fresh pizza and they're quick to have it ready for you when you walk in.  I'm sure they have good management since they've hired workers that appear to have better attitude than most I have seen in Orlando.

name: Erik Toner
text: My wife is a native Californian (SF Bay Area-East Bay), and I l lived in California for 5 1/2 years (also Bay Area), so we were ecstatic when Papa Murphy's finally made it to Central Florida - even though the closest place is over 60 miles …More

name: brandi Jodon
text: Our go to for pizza last time they were a little skimpy on the prices and it took a little longer but will always go back

name: Joseph Smith
text: Cook your own pizza. They make a good one.

name: Brian Hall
text: We enjoy the take a bake pizzas from Papa Murphys. They also have gluten-free crust on some of their pizza options so if you have friends or family you need to accommodate for you have options here.

name: Valerie Shortt
text: Fresh ingredients! Delicious food @ a reasonable price and friendly customer service! I was hooked the first time I went!

name: Alante' Fuller
text: Yummy can't stop coming here... About a 25-30 min drive but it's my new pizza place

name: Mike Milbauer
text: The pizza is great. The service is very good and they're very polite.

name: Jennifer Davis
text: Yuuuummmmy. Bake it at home so it is fresh. Made to order so its just what you want.

name: Emma Torres
text: Excellent Pizza. I first did not know you had to take it home and bake it but its so worth it!!! 10/10

name: Robert Beistel
text: I was not impressed at all. I would rather get a pizza at Ginos on Alafaya instead.

name: BigBoss
text: Oh my God I'm going to be coming here a lot more often! GREAT PIZZA!

name: Erin Compton
text: The take n bake concept is awesome and they have delicious pizza! So glad we tried it out!

name: Nick Ivey
text: Beautiful Store, Great staff and can't beat Papa Murphy's Pizza!

name: Chris Kunze
text: Always fast and fresh, and the staff is very friendly

name: John Malloy
text: Very yummy. Reasonably priced, but definitely towards more expensive.

name: Stacey
text: Fast and friendly

name: Charles Farides
text: Never a bad pizza.

name: GamerFan 6363
text: Love there pizza

name: David Dwyer
text: Halloween Pizzas is the new, easy tradition.

name: Kimbra Monson
text: Great Staff and Pizza!! Love the Steak and Roasted Garlic Pizza!!

name: MrMzPotts
text: It's okay

name: Jessica Beeson
text: great customer service

name: pahornback
text: Love it

name: Jeanette Heideman
text: Very handy and delicious

name: Lawrence Wachter
text: Stuffed Pizza is the way to go.

name: Christopher Felker
text: Love there fresh pizza

name: John Esposito
text: I can tell you for a fact This place is spotless clean, always a good thing when it comes to Food!

name: Dedra Jenkins
text: Love it!

name: Jacquelyn Lynn
text: Great pizza, excellent staff.

name: Benay Derdemez
text: BEST Pizza! Friendly Staff and Excellent Offers!!

name: Dozur
text: How do you get the prices so you know if you want to order or not?????????????????
